    "news":"The Cabinet Committee on Security (CCS) chaired by Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Wednesday approved the acquisition of critical training platforms for the Navy and the Indian Air Force (IAF) — including three cadet training ships from the Larsen & Toubro Limited (L&T), and 70 Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL)-made HTT-40 Basic Trainer Aircraft.As per the defence ministry, the CCS accorded approval to sign a contract with L&T for the acquisition of three cadet training ships worth Rs 3,108.09 crore. The ships will be procured under the Buy Indian-IDDM (indigenously designed, developed and manufactured) category of the defence acquisition procedure—the manual governing all defence capital procurements. ",
